messages.content:
Implement `request_options` parameter on `send_message` — structured option buttons in the approval UI, with guard enforcement.

**Work inside:** `.synapse/worktrees/developer-25-request-options`
Commit all changes in one commit. Do not push. Report DONE to cec50b17:0.

---

## Overview

When an agent sends a message to `human` with `needs_approval: true`, it may now also pass `request_options: string[]` — a list of choices for the operator. The UI renders clickable option buttons instead of the free-text reply input. Clicking an option marks it selected, sends it as a reply to the agent, and marks the message approved.

The free-text `approval-reply-input` from the previous implementation should be **removed** and replaced by this structured system.

---

## 1. DB (`src/db.ts`)

Add two migrations:
```ts
`ALTER TABLE messages ADD COLUMN request_options TEXT`,      // JSON array of option strings, nullable
`ALTER TABLE messages ADD COLUMN selected_option INTEGER`,   // index into request_options, nullable
```

Update `Message` interface:
```ts
request_options: string | null;   // stored as JSON, parse client-side
selected_option: number | null;
```

Update `sendMessage()` function signature to accept `options?: string[]`:
```ts
export function sendMessage(
  fromId: string, toId: string, content: string,
  priority: number, needsApproval = false, options?: string[]
): number
```
In the INSERT, add `request_options` column: `options ? JSON.stringify(options) : null`.

Add new function:
```ts
export function selectOption(messageId: number, optionIndex: number): void {
  db.prepare(`UPDATE messages SET selected_option = ?, approved_at = ? WHERE id = ?`)
    .run(optionIndex, Date.now(), messageId);
}
```

---

## 2. MCP server (`src/mcp-server.ts`)

Add `request_options` to `send_message` tool schema:
```ts
request_options: {
  type: 'array',
  items: { type: 'string' },
  description: 'Optional list of choices to present to the operator as clickable buttons. ' +
    'Use when the message requires the operator to pick one of several options. ' +
    'Requires needs_approval: true.',
},
```

Update tool description to mention `request_options`.

In the handler, destructure and pass to `sendMessage`:
```ts
const { to_id, content, priority = 5, report_file = false, needs_approval = false, request_options } = args as {
  ...
  request_options?: string[];
};
// pass to sendMessage:
sendMessage(AGENT_ID, to_id, content, priority, needs_approval, request_options);
```

---

## 3. Guard (`src/hooks/guard.ts`)

Add a lint check: if `to_id === 'human'` and `needs_approval === true` and `content` contains numbered options (matches `/^\d+\./m` or `/^[-•]\s/m` or contains "option 1" / "option 2" patterns) but `request_options` is absent or empty — deny:

```ts
if (tool === 'mcp__synapse-bus__send_message') {
  const toId = String(input.to_id ?? '');
  if (!('needs_approval' in input)) {
    return deny('needs_approval is required when messaging human...');
  }
  // existing check ↑ stays

  // NEW: if needs_approval and content looks like it has options, require request_options
  const needsApproval = input.needs_approval === true;
  const content = String(input.content ?? '');
  const hasOptions = Array.isArray(input.request_options) && input.request_options.length > 0;
  if (toId === 'human' && needsApproval && !hasOptions && looksLikeOptionList(content)) {
    return deny(
      'This message presents options to the human but request_options is not set. ' +
      'Pass request_options: ["option 1 text", "option 2 text"] so the operator sees clickable buttons.'
    );
  }
  return allow();
}

function looksLikeOptionList(content: string): boolean {
  return /^\s*\d+[.)]/m.test(content) || /^[-•]\s/m.test(content);
}
```

---

## 4. Dashboard API (`src/dashboard.ts`)

Add endpoint:
```ts
app.post('/api/messages/:id/select-option', (req, res) => {
  const id = parseInt(req.params.id, 10);
  const { option_index, reply_to } = req.body as { option_index: number; reply_to: string };
  selectOption(id, option_index);
  // Also send the option text as a reply to the agent
  // (get the message to find the option text and from_id)
  res.json({ ok: true });
});
```

Actually simpler: have the frontend send the reply message itself (POST /api/messages) and call the select endpoint separately. Just implement:
```ts
app.post('/api/messages/:id/select-option', (req, res) => {
  const id = parseInt(req.params.id, 10);
  const { option_index } = req.body as { option_index: number };
  selectOption(id, option_index);
  res.json({ ok: true });
});
```

Import `selectOption` from db.

---

## 5. Frontend (`public/app.js`)

**Remove** the `approval-reply-input` and its handling from the delegated click handler and the `approveBtn` template.

**Update `approveBtn` template:**

```js
const approveBtn = (!fromHuman && m.needs_approval)
  ? (() => {
      if (m.approved_at !== null && m.approved_at !== undefined) {
        // Already approved — show what was selected or generic badge
        const opts = m.request_options ? JSON.parse(m.request_options) : null;
        const badge = (opts && m.selected_option != null)
          ? `<span class="msg-approved-badge">✓ ${esc(opts[m.selected_option])}</span>`
          : `<span class="msg-approved-badge">✓ approved</span>`;
        return `<div class="message-actions">${badge}</div>`;
      }
      const opts = m.request_options ? JSON.parse(m.request_options) : null;
      if (opts && opts.length > 0) {
        // Show option buttons
        const btns = opts.map((opt, i) =>
          `<button class="msg-option-btn" data-msg-id="${m.id}" data-option-index="${i}" data-from-id="${esc(m.from_id)}" data-priority="${m.priority}">${esc(opt)}</button>`
        ).join('');
        return `<div class="message-actions message-options">${btns}</div>`;
      }
      // No options — plain approve button (no text input)
      return `<div class="message-actions"><button class="msg-approve-btn" data-msg-id="${m.id}">✓ approve</button></div>`;
    })()
  : '';
```

**Update delegated click handler** on `#messages-list` to handle `.msg-option-btn`:
```js
messagesList.addEventListener('click', async (e) => {
  // existing approve btn handler
  const approveBtn = e.target.closest('.msg-approve-btn');
  if (approveBtn) {
    approveBtn.disabled = true;
    approveBtn.textContent = '✓ approved';
    await fetch(`/api/messages/${approveBtn.dataset.msgId}/approve`, { method: 'POST' });
    return;
  }
  // new option btn handler
  const optBtn = e.target.closest('.msg-option-btn');
  if (optBtn) {
    const { msgId, optionIndex, fromId, priority } = optBtn.dataset;
    optBtn.closest('.message-actions').querySelectorAll('.msg-option-btn').forEach(b => b.disabled = true);
    optBtn.classList.add('selected');
    await Promise.all([
      fetch(`/api/messages/${msgId}/select-option`, {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
        body: JSON.stringify({ option_index: parseInt(optionIndex, 10) }),
      }),
      fetch('/api/messages', {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
        body: JSON.stringify({ to_id: fromId, content: optBtn.textContent, priority: parseInt(priority, 10) }),
      }),
    ]);
  }
});
```

